This paper deals with the performance analysis of a cooperative relaying system in the presence of interference, which is a common problem in wireless communication networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also considers the spatial distribution of the interferers, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The analysis of the system performance involves statistical modeling and optimization, which are relevant to the categories cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MA (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper uses Rayleigh fading, which is a common model in wireless communication, and discusses the tradeoff between energy efficiency and throughput, which are relevant to the category cs.MM (Multimedia).
